<p><b>Directions and Trailheads</b>- To get to French Creek from Reading take Highway 422 east to Rt. 82 south. Follow 82 into the little town of Birdsboro and take a left at the light onto Rt. 724. Follow 724 for about 1 mile and turn right onto Rt. 345, you'll pass a supermarket on your right. 345 takes you into the heart of the park.</p>
<p>There is a popular trailhead at the intersection of 345 and Shed Rd. This is where the Lenape trail connects with the Mill Creek trail and is the only spot where the east and west trail networks meet for mountain bikes. (Other trails connect on the furnace lands but bikes are prohibited from these trails.)</p>
<p>There are also parking lots by Hopewell Lake, Scott's Run Lake, and the gate at Fire Tower Rd.</p>

